BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed MAR: "Crisis: Belgian Ambassador's </F>
Departure Confirmed"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 12 Apr (BELGA) -- The Belgian Foreign 
Ministry officially confirmed Tuesday evening [12 April] that 
"it instructed Belgian Ambassador in Rwanda Johan Swinnen to 
leave the country for security reasons." 
  Five members of the embassy will remain temporarily on duty 
at Kigali airport. They will leave the Rwandan capital when the 
evacuation is over, the Foreign Ministry added. 

